the $ron you own today.  

You own the rights to earn more passive $ron tomorrow.

Today, the $ron network is valued at $333 million.

You can say the fully diluted value is a more realistic valuation ($2.24 billion), but owning part of the $ron pool when user validating/staking gets turned on gives you access to more passive $ron.

So you don't just own..

Now imagine @Ronin_Network reaches mass appeal with billions of users.  

What is owning a percentage of the network bandwidth of something that size worth?

Not saying that global domination is guaranteed, but I don't think anyone else is positioned to achieve it more quickly.

Your $ron will give you rights to stake or delegate your tokens for more tokens in exchange for securing the network.  

Accumulating a position in $ron today means your right to earn more tokens through validating tomorrow.

A right to be a toll booth on @Ronin_Network.

Eventually, there will be many games on Ronin.

Imagine it's 2025.  

Imagine there are now 50 games on Ronin.  

Imagine hundreds of millions of users and the liquidity that comes with numbers like that.

Think longer term.

Buying $ron right now could be compared to buying the $eth presale, but for the @Ronin_Network.

$ron is network fuel just like $eth.  

Eventually, every transaction performed (excluding free txs, which will be turned down) on Ronin will require $ron.

Think longer term.
